<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Working with SQL files</b></p><p>Double-click an SQL file to open it in the IDE. To run a query from this file, call intention actions (Option+Enter for macOS, Alt+Enter for Windows and Linux) and select <span class="control">Run query in console</span>. In the <span class="control">Sessions</span> list, select existed console or create a new one.</p><p>Note that a new query console means a new connection to a data source.</p><p class="image"><img src="images/db_pl_tips_DBRunQueryIntention.png" alt="Intention action to run a query in a query console" style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p></body></html>